<TITLE> Ex-Bogra BNP MP Lalu jailed for 5 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)  A Bogra court Monday sentenced former BNP lawmaker Helaluzzaman Talukdar Lalu to five years in prison for illegally installing wireless communication tower at his home. Judge Golam Ahmed Khalilur Rahman of Bogra District and Sessions Judge's Court-2 handed down the verdict which also fined the convict Tk 5 lakh. Lalu would be liable to serve another six months in prison if he does not pay the money, the court said. His lawyer Mir Iqbal said they would move the higher court against the verdict. The former lawmaker, currently serving a one-year jail sentence for misappropriating CI sheets meant for relief, was in the dock when the judgment was delivered. Security forces arrested Lalu on Feb 13 in a raid on his 'Champa Mahal' home in Bogra town and retrieved the corrugated iron sheets. A wireless tower was also found to have been illegally installed at the house. Police filed two cases after the raid. Lalu faces a number of other cases charging him with extortion. bdnews24.
